workflow.name: Build a multi-agent system with n8n, Qdrant, Gmail & OpenAI
workflow.description:
This template presents a multi-agent system in which a coordinating agent manages specialized sub-agents: **an AI agent for RAG** and document summarization, and **an email agent**. Each agent effectively operates in its own domain, working collaboratively under the management of the primary agent.

In addition to the two sub-agents, the coordinator agent queries the latest news by calling the [HTTPS Request Tool]( https://docs.n8n.io/integrations/builtin/cluster-nodes/sub-nodes/n8n-nodes-langchain.toolhttprequest/).

üí° This template is an extended version of the initial workflow on how to [Build a RAG Agent with n8n, Qdrant & OpenAI]( https://creators.n8n.io/workflows/11468). 

The RAG sub-agent can use the [same Qdrant collection](https://drive.google.com/drive/u/2/folders/1BevhU5qdgNDFbK4D9oAYGeK0Dt5sEaxQ). You can import this example collection (n8n-rag-2437367325990310-2025-11-04-10-41-54.snapshot) of 3 documents into the free Qdrant cloud or self-hosted account, rather than creating it from scratch.

## üîóExample files for RAG 

The template uses the following **example files** in the Google Docs format:
1. German Data Protection law: Bundesdatenschutzgesetz (BDSG)
2. Computer Security Incident Handling Guide (NIST.SP.800-61r2)
3. Berkshire Hathaway letter to shareholders from 2024 

## üöÄHow to Get Started

1. Copy or import the template to your n8n instance.
2. Create your **Google Drive credentials** via the Google Cloud Console and add them to the "Get Document" node. A detailed walk-through can be found in the n8n [docs](https://docs.n8n.io/integrations/builtin/credentials/google/oauth-single-service/).
3. Create your **Gmail credentials** via the Google Cloud Console and add them to the Gmail nodes. 
4. Create a [Qdrant API](https://qdrant.tech/) key and add it to the "Search Documents" node credentials. The API key will be displayed after you have logged into Qdrant and created a Cluster.
5. Create or activate your [OpenAI API]( https://platform.openai.com/api-keys) key.
6. Create or activate your [OpenRouter API]( https://openrouter.ai/docs/api/reference/authentication) key. 
7. Create or activate your [News API]( https://newsapi.org/) key.

## üí¨Chat with the main Agent to query document data, search latest news or perform Email actions

1Ô∏è‚É£ Ask the agent about specific information, facts, quotes, or details that are stored in the uploaded documents. 

*E.g. What should be documented during incident response?*

2Ô∏è‚É£ Ask the agent about recent news and current information from web sources. 

*E.g. What does BDSG say about data breaches and are there any recent cases?*

3Ô∏è‚É£ Ask the agent to summarize the document or information related to the documents and email it to you. 

*E.g.I need a short summary of the Berkshire Hathaway letter, please send it to my email [user@example.com].*

4Ô∏è‚É£ Aks the agent to update you on your recent emails.

*E.g. I‚Äôd like to know the content of the latest email from [username].*

5Ô∏è‚É£ Ask the agent to create a draft of the email.

*E.g. Please create an email draft of the [document] summary.*

## üåüAdapt this template for your own use case

- **Enterprise workflows** - Google Docs processing with automated communications 
- **Research teams** - Document analysis with automatic report distribution 
- **Customer success** - Intelligent document search with follow-up email automation 
- **Content operations** - Document summarization with stakeholder notifications 
- **Compliance workflows** - Policy queries with automated alert systems

**‚ö†Ô∏è The current multi-agent architecture comes with certain trade-offs: the sequential nature of agent hand-offs can increase latency compared to single calls, and the full conversation history is not shared between all sub-agents.**

üíª üìû[Get in touch](https://www.linkedin.com/in/yulia-dmitrievna-1112361b5/) if you want to customise this workflow or have any questions.

messageValues.message: You are an expert summarizer. Summarize the provided document(s) (from a vector database), focusing on key points relevant to the user's query.

options.systemMessage:
=You are a helpful AI assistant with access to a document knowledge base. Your primary role is to answer user questions based strictly on the information found in the documents.

CRITICAL: You MUST use the document search tool for ANY question that could be answered from documents, even if you think you know the answer from your training data.

Guidelines:
- ALWAYS search the document knowledge base first before answering questions
- Even if a question seems general, check the documents first - they may contain specific information
- Base your answers ONLY on information retrieved from the documents
- If the documents contain relevant information, use it and ALWAYS CITE the source with a link
- If you cannot find the answer in the documents after searching, clearly state: "I searched the available documents but could not find this specific information"
- NEVER answer factual questions from your general knowledge if they could relate to document content
- If the user's question is unclear, ask for clarification
- When providing factual information (dates, numbers, names, specific facts), include a SHORT direct quote from the document to verify accuracy
- Format quotes like this: "According to the document: '[exact quote]'"
- Keep quotes concise - just enough to verify the specific fact

Be accurate, concise, and honest about the limitations of the available information.

Always include brief quotes for factual claims.

Remember: Your purpose is to help users find information IN THE DOCUMENTS, not to provide general knowledge. Always search first. The documents may contain specific information that differs from general knowledge.

IMPORTANT for broad questions:
- Questions like "Do any documents mention X?" or "Which documents discuss Y?" require checking ALL relevant documents
- Review search results carefully - multiple documents may contain relevant information
- If you find information in one document, check if others also mention the topic
- Acknowledge ALL documents that contain relevant information, not just the first one you find

The knowledge base contains business correspondence, legal documents, and technical guides. Use the search tool to find relevant information from these sources.

When answering:
- Provide direct answers first
- Reference the source document (e.g., "According to the NIST guidelines...")
- Use bullet points for multiple pieces of information
- ALWAYS CITE the source in the following format: Source: ...

If the user asks about the news, call the HTTP Requst tool.

If user asks to summarize a document or information relevant to the document:
  ‚Üí Call Sub-Workflow tool
  ‚Üí Return summary

If you are asked for a summary, please provide only the summary you receive from the workflow tool. Send the user exactly the summary you receive from the workflow tool under the heading "Summary." Do not analyze or modify it; send it back to the user.

options.systemMessage:
=You are a Multi-Agent Coordinator responsible for managing specialized sub-agents to answer user questions comprehensively.

AVAILABLE SUB-AGENTS:
1. RAG Agent - Searches and analyzes documents (Berkshire Hathaway letters, BDSG law, NIST guidelines). Can also generate document summaries.
2. Gmail Agent - Handles email communications (sends messages, reads inbox, creates drafts, manages multiple messages). If the user asks you to send the summary by email, always call the email sub-agent.
3. News HTTP Request Tool - Fetches recent news and current information from web sources. This tool should ONLY be called when the user explicitly requests updates; do not call it if the user needs the information available in the documents.

YOUR ROLE:
- Analyze user requests to determine which sub-agent(s) are needed
- Route questions to appropriate specialists
- Coordinate between multiple agents when needed
- Synthesize responses from sub-agents into coherent answers
- Maintain conversation context and follow up appropriately

DECISION LOGIC:
- Document-related questions ‚Üí RAG Document Agent
- Email requests or communication needs ‚Üí Email Agent  
- Current events, recent data, news ‚Üí News HTTP Request Tool
- Complex questions may require multiple agents

If the user asks you to send the summary via email, always call the email sub-agent.

parameters.toolDescription: Use HTTP for news OR ANY RECENT CASES on user query.

parameters.content:
## Gmail sub-agent
Reads, send emails and creates drafts.

## RAG sub-agent
Searches documents in **Qdrant vector database** and prepares document summaries.

## Full document summarization
Retrieves documents from the [Google Drive folder](https://drive.google.com/drive/u/2/folders/1BevhU5qdgNDFbK4D9oAYGeK0Dt5sEaxQ) and generates summaries.

## Main AI Agent
Routes user queries to the corresponding Tools (**RAG** and **Gmail** sub-agents, **news tool**).

# Build a Multi-Agent system with n8n, Qdrant, Gmail & OpenAI

## How it works
**AI Agent** receives user queries and routes them to specialized **sub-agents** or a **news tool**:

1. **RAG sub-agent** searches documents in **Qdrant vector database** and prepares a summary via a sub-workflow.
2. **Email sub-agent** performs Gmail actions (read and send emails, create drafts).
3. [The HTTP Request Tool](https://docs.n8n.io/integrations/builtin/cluster-nodes/sub-nodes/n8n-nodes-langchain.toolhttprequest/) fetches current news via the dedicated API.

## How to set up
### 1. Import the template to your n8n instance and set up **credentials**
- Google Drive & Gmail (via Google Cloud Console)
- [Qdrant API](https://qdrant.tech/) key (create a Cluster first)
- [OpenAI](https://platform.openai.com/api-keys), [OpenRouter](https://openrouter.ai/docs/api/reference/authentication), and 
- [News API](https://newsapi.org/) keys

### 2. Import the example [Qdrant collection](https://drive.google.com/drive/u/2/folders/1BevhU5qdgNDFbK4D9oAYGeK0Dt5sEaxQ)
- The collection is saved under the name **n8n-rag-2437367325990310-2025-11-04-10-41-54.snapshot**. 
- Alternatively, you can upload your own documents.

### 3. Chat with the Agent
Ask the Agent to search documents, prepare a summary, check emails or fetch latest news.

## News Tool
Fetches latest news via API.
